{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, AI-backed electronic noses and tongues offer automated and objective alternatives for sensory evaluation.",
    "These systems integrate sensor arrays with machine learning algorithms to detect and classify odor and taste patterns.",
    "In terms of sensitivity, AI-driven platforms can identify subtle variations in volatile or taste-active compounds that may not be discernible to human assessors.",
    "For instance, recent studies have demonstrated that machine learning models trained on sensor responses can detect food spoilage, off-flavors, or adulteration with higher consistency than sensory panels.",
    "Regarding specificity, while traditional chemical analysis remains superior in isolating individual molecules, AI systems can achieve functional specificity by learning from data patterns across complex mixtures."
  ]
}